0.2
=====

* Use of Gecko instead of Gnome.Canvas. It's much faster and easier to code.
* New music Albums catalog.
* New Export feature. You can export your catalogs to HTML.
* New Search Engine motor.
* Search engines:
	* Amazon
	* IMDB
* Performance improvements, bugfixes and code cleanups.

0.1
=====

* Now it's possible to change the order of the shelf. You can order by
    any field of the item, ascending or descending.
* Each catalogs saves his state in the database.
* Double click on empty space at shelf view shows the New Item dialog.
* Performance improvements.

0.0.6
=====

* Minor bugfixes.

0.0.5
=====

* Double click on items (both in shelf and list views) shows the Edit dialog.
* Fixed lots of small bugs.
* Updates the database version if needed.
* Improvements to the database.

0.0.4
=====

* Lots of performance improvements.
* Fixed some bugs about the Amazon Web Service.
* Fixed UI bugs.

0.0.3
=====

* Bugfix release.
* Lots of bugfixes in the autotools scripts.
* Minor changes in the UI.

0.0.2
=====

* Added themes support.
* Improved the overview view with zoom support.
* Added i18n support.
* Added autotools scripts.
* Removed all the monodevelop stuff.

0.0.1
=====

* First release
